President Obama has declared a major disaster in Tennessee due to severe storms, flooding, winds, and tornadoes. Federal funding will be provided to affected individuals and counties for temporary housing, home repairs, and other assistance programs. Federal funding is also available for debris removal, emergency protective measures, and hazard mitigation statewide. Gracia B. Szczech has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Damage surveys are ongoing, and additional assistance may be designated after assessments are completed. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance online or by phone.